<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,537,151,176]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Distribution and bionomics.</emphasis>
This species was taken in mid-elevation (
<quantity box="[1023,1174,152,176]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" metricValueMax="2.2" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" unit="m" value="2100.0" valueMax="2200.0" valueMin="2000.0">2000–2200m</quantity>
) of northern to central mountain regions in 
<collectingCountry box="[387,472,188,213]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, the vegetation of the two collecting localities are primary broad-leaved forests. The adults only found in February.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="431" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,320]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named after the late Tadao Kano (
<date box="[756,889,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="431" value="1906" valueMax="1945">1906–1945</date>
?), one of the famous explorers and pioneering scientists studying on 
<collectingCountry box="[399,481,295,320]" name="Taiwan" pageId="6" pageNumber="431">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
natural history.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
